You don't seem too excited.

541
00:48:20,940 --> 00:48:22,560
Who's your date?

542
00:48:22,770 --> 00:48:24,430
Todd's old girlfriend.

543
00:48:26,660 --> 00:48:27,940
Sorry.

544
00:48:28,000 --> 00:48:29,510
It's okay.

545
00:48:30,240 --> 00:48:32,100
I'll just pretend
It's somebody else.

546
00:48:35,650 --> 00:48:37,720
Maybe next time
you could work it out

547
00:48:38,140 --> 00:48:39,720
so you won't have to pretend.

548
00:48:42,070 --> 00:48:43,510
Yeah,

549
00:48:43,990 --> 00:48:45,480
maybe...

550
00:48:46,000 --> 00:48:47,540
see you later.

551
00:48:50,140 --> 00:48:51,720
Bye.

552
00:48:59,360 --> 00:49:01,730
That was an interesting
conversation.

553
00:49:02,360 --> 00:49:03,960
You heard all that?

554
00:49:04,280 --> 00:49:05,880
Sure, I heard it.

555
00:49:08,790 --> 00:49:10,860
I didn't understand it,
though.
Good.

556
00:49:12,240 --> 00:49:15,080
No, what I mean is, If Blake's
the one you like,

557
00:49:15,360 --> 00:49:17,680
why are you going out with
T-T-Todd tonight?

558
00:49:18,320 --> 00:49:19,680
I don't get it.

559
00:49:19,780 --> 00:49:21,680
Well, the way I look at it is,

560
00:49:21,780 --> 00:49:23,250
I go out with him tonight,

561
00:49:23,370 --> 00:49:25,010
have a terrible time,

562
00:49:25,200 --> 00:49:26,910
and then, maybe he'll leave
me alone.

563
00:49:28,340 --> 00:49:30,370
And since we're going to
a dance

564
00:49:30,550 --> 00:49:33,490
and we're all going together,
then, you know...

565
00:49:33,940 --> 00:49:35,740
maybe I'll get to spend some
time with Blake.

566
00:49:37,070 --> 00:49:39,450
See how complicated
being a girl is.

567
00:49:47,020 --> 00:49:48,310
Remember the deal now.

568
00:49:48,380 --> 00:49:50,880
No playing tricks on Jane When
she comes home from her date.

569
00:49:50,990 --> 00:49:52,260
Promise?

570
00:49:52,350 --> 00:49:53,960
I promise.

571
00:49:55,790 --> 00:49:57,570
Doesn't mean we can't spy
on 'em.

572
00:50:03,470 --> 00:50:05,600
Hey, Oscar, can I ask you
something?

573
00:50:06,320 --> 00:50:07,720
Okay.

574
00:50:08,050 --> 00:50:10,860
How come you always want
to meet down at the cemetery?

575
00:50:12,540 --> 00:50:14,180
Because I like it.

576
00:50:15,180 --> 00:50:16,770
Oh, yeah, I know.

577
00:50:17,250 --> 00:50:19,980
But how come you don't ever
want to meet anywhere else?

578
00:50:21,040 --> 00:50:22,900
Like at the lookout or
something?

579
00:50:24,430 --> 00:50:26,700
It's not okay at cemetery?

580
00:50:27,390 --> 00:50:28,960
No, it's okay.

581
00:50:29,770 --> 00:50:31,430
It's just
not normal.

582
00:50:32,200 --> 00:50:33,770
You know what I mean?

583
00:50:34,320 --> 00:50:37,310
It's not normal to like to be
around dead people.

584
00:50:37,710 --> 00:50:38,970
Why?

585
00:50:39,050 --> 00:50:41,460
Because they're spooky.

586
00:50:41,930 --> 00:50:43,340
Why?

587
00:50:43,570 --> 00:50:45,930
Because they're dead.

588
00:50:47,530 --> 00:50:50,270
My grandmother dead and
she no spoky.

589
00:50:50,820 --> 00:50:52,250
Spoo-ky.

590
00:50:53,040 --> 00:50:54,590
Spoo-ky.

591
00:50:55,170 --> 00:50:56,700
She's not.

592
00:50:56,860 --> 00:50:59,030
But your grandma isn't
in that cemetery.

593
00:51:00,790 --> 00:51:02,620
But when I go there,

594
00:51:04,060 --> 00:51:06,100
I feel like she is there.

595
00:51:07,470 --> 00:51:09,430
My grandma died last year.

596
00:51:10,990 --> 00:51:12,480
I'm sorry.

597
00:51:13,660 --> 00:51:16,290
Where is your grandmother
buried?

598
00:51:18,550 --> 00:51:20,260
In the cemetery in by town.

599
00:51:20,920 --> 00:51:23,820
Do you think that cemetery
is spooky, too?

600
00:51:24,760 --> 00:51:26,230
Yeah, I guess.

601
00:51:26,700 --> 00:51:28,180
It's kinda creepy.

602
00:51:28,280 --> 00:51:29,590
Creaky?

603
00:51:29,690 --> 00:51:31,530
Cree-py.

604
00:51:32,830 --> 00:51:34,650
You know, spoo-ky.

605
00:51:38,660 --> 00:51:40,300
Do you like your grandmother?

606
00:51:41,230 --> 00:51:42,600
Uh huh.

607
00:51:43,150 --> 00:51:44,680
I like my grandma a lot.

608
00:51:46,180 --> 00:51:48,000
Did you go visit her?

609
00:51:48,770 --> 00:51:50,270
At the cemetery?

610
00:51:51,620 --> 00:51:53,170
Well, no.

611
00:51:53,870 --> 00:51:55,420
You should.

612
00:51:56,040 --> 00:51:58,120
It lets you feel quiet.

613
00:51:59,830 --> 00:52:01,250
Quiet?

614
00:52:03,200 --> 00:52:04,690
Inside.

615
00:52:11,390 --> 00:52:12,910
You're not normal, too.

616
00:52:13,280 --> 00:52:15,540
I'm not normal?
No, you're not.

617
00:52:17,200 --> 00:52:18,950
What's not normal about me?

618
00:52:19,270 --> 00:52:20,660
You live like boys do.

619
00:52:20,760 --> 00:52:22,510
I like living like a boy.

620
00:52:24,110 --> 00:52:26,300
I'm gonna have to be a girl
soon enough.

621
00:52:26,950 --> 00:52:29,140
You don't even use girl's name.

622
00:52:29,310 --> 00:52:31,920
Your real name is Iris.

623
00:52:32,550 --> 00:52:34,040
Who told you that?

624
00:52:45,530 --> 00:52:47,080
They're back early.

625
00:52:58,960 --> 00:53:00,930
Come on, Jane!
Calm down, will ya?

626
00:53:01,900 --> 00:53:03,530
I brought you home.
I should have walked.

627
00:53:03,590 --> 00:53:05,730
You're not giving me a chance...
To what?

628
00:53:05,870 --> 00:53:08,440
I don't know, to say something.
To say something?

629
00:53:08,810 --> 00:53:12,190
What you need to do, Todd,  is keep
your mouth shut and not say so much.

630
00:53:12,280 --> 00:53:14,760
I don't understand why you
get so mad about what I said.

631
00:53:14,860 --> 00:53:16,890
Because I'm sick of hearing
it, that why.

632
00:53:16,970 --> 00:53:20,050
I am sick of hearing about
what you want to do to anybody...

633
00:53:20,140 --> 00:53:21,480
who isn't just like you are.

634
00:53:21,560 --> 00:53:22,990
So?
So?!

635
00:53:23,540 --> 00:53:26,670
As far as I concerned you're just
like all those people on TV...

636
00:53:26,760 --> 00:53:30,070
all those people who throw bricks
and set fires and hurt people!

637
00:53:30,140 --> 00:53:31,580
What are you talking about?

638
00:53:32,450 --> 00:53:33,740
Nevermind!

639
00:53:33,840 --> 00:53:37,180
I honestly don't think you're smart
enough to know what I am talking about.

640
00:53:38,770 --> 00:53:41,490
What? You don't think I could
do the things I say I do?

641
00:53:41,810 --> 00:53:44,780
No, that's not what I'm talking
about, but suit your brother...

642
00:53:44,870 --> 00:53:46,170
But let me tell you what I think.

643
00:53:46,240 --> 00:53:48,860
I think if you and your goons
ever got a chance to do anything,

644
00:53:48,930 --> 00:53:52,010
any of those people around
you'd all get your faces kicked in.

645
00:53:52,070 --> 00:53:53,390
Is that right?
That's right!

646
00:53:53,480 --> 00:53:55,350
Does that go for your beaner
boyfriend, too?

647
00:53:55,500 --> 00:53:57,340
I don't have a beaner boyfriend.

648
00:53:57,620 --> 00:54:00,080
But if you're talking about a
certain person that works here,

649
00:54:00,170 --> 00:54:02,140
I'd say that goes especially
for him.

650
00:54:04,290 --> 00:54:05,790
I'm gonna walk home.

651
00:54:12,310 --> 00:54:14,460
That was incredible.

652
00:54:16,670 --> 00:54:18,160
Are we leaving?

653
00:54:20,050 --> 00:54:21,530
Yup, we're leavin'.

654
00:54:31,820 --> 00:54:33,430
What a show!

655
00:54:34,350 --> 00:54:37,790
Remind me never to get Jane
that mad at me.

656
00:54:38,240 --> 00:54:40,900
She ate Todd up and spit
him out.

657
00:54:41,480 --> 00:54:44,080
I can see pieces of him all
over the driveway.

658
00:54:47,100 --> 00:54:48,720
Hey, where you goin'?

659
00:54:49,760 --> 00:54:51,200
It time to go.

660
00:54:53,720 --> 00:54:55,000
You all right?

661
00:54:55,110 --> 00:54:56,470
All right, yes.

662
00:54:56,600 --> 00:54:58,420
I'll see you tomorrow.

663
00:55:04,460 --> 00:55:06,000
What is this, huh?

664
00:55:06,080 --> 00:55:08,500
Get a little soft,
huh, Blakey boy.

665
00:55:09,840 --> 00:55:11,510
Why don't you go back up
there to Jane

666
00:55:11,580 --> 00:55:13,250
and tell her how great you
are now.

667
00:55:13,430 --> 00:55:15,170
Yeah, she'll cuddle
right up to ya.

668
00:55:16,520 --> 00:55:19,040
Come on, this is your big
chance to win her heart.

669
00:55:21,620 --> 00:55:23,820
Okay, fine, walk home and
don't say anything.

670
00:55:23,930 --> 00:55:26,460
It's no skin off my nose.
All right. I'll say something.

671
00:55:29,130 --> 00:55:30,660
Jane is right!

672
00:55:37,480 --> 00:55:39,370
Get out!
What?

673
00:55:39,630 --> 00:55:41,220
Get out, I said.
Hurry up!

674
00:55:41,290 --> 00:55:42,610
Randy?
Todd?

675
00:55:42,690 --> 00:55:44,340
Shut up! Look, get out
right now!

676
00:55:44,410 --> 00:55:46,050
Make couple seconds or you're
gonna be trapped...

677
00:55:46,130 --> 00:55:47,660
And you're not gonna like it!

678
00:55:47,730 --> 00:55:49,180
Come on!

679
00:55:53,800 --> 00:55:55,590
So, you think Jane was
right, huh?

680
00:55:55,890 --> 00:55:57,580
Well, let's find out.
What are you gonna do?

681
00:55:57,730 --> 00:55:59,190
Watch!

682
00:55:59,520 --> 00:56:00,880
Todd!

683
00:56:10,100 --> 00:56:11,710
Ira, go get your dad!

684
00:56:12,010 --> 00:56:14,200
What's goin' on?
Just go get him.

685
00:56:14,360 --> 00:56:15,680
Hurry!

686
00:56:15,750 --> 00:56:17,260
Todd, don't do this!

687
00:56:17,340 --> 00:56:19,030
This isn't right.
Shut up!

688
00:56:21,500 --> 00:56:23,710
What's goin' on?
Todd's gone crazy.

689
00:56:46,820 --> 00:56:48,830
This isn't just calling names
and picking fights.

690
00:56:48,970 --> 00:56:51,050
This is bad, Todd, come on!
Shu up!

691
00:56:52,830 --> 00:56:54,250
Oscar!

692
00:57:06,780 --> 00:57:08,170
Come on!

693
00:57:08,250 --> 00:57:10,450
You wanna kick my face in now?
Come on!

694
00:57:14,190 --> 00:57:15,980
Come on! Come on, hurry up!

695
00:57:25,770 --> 00:57:27,340
There's Todd's car.

696
00:57:43,710 --> 00:57:45,250
Down here.

697
00:57:48,970 --> 00:57:50,860
I'll get an ambulance.
There's no time for that.

698
00:57:51,580 --> 00:57:53,800
Let's get him out. Right.
Be carefull.

699
00:57:54,790 --> 00:57:56,350
Let's get him in the back.

700
00:58:12,010 --> 00:58:13,480
I'll go get Todd.

701
00:58:27,380 --> 00:58:29,000
George, what happened?

702
00:58:29,070 --> 00:58:31,600
I don't have time to explain.
Just get in and get us to the hospital.

703
00:58:35,160 --> 00:58:37,220
I wanna go, too.
Ira, please stay.

704
00:58:56,740 --> 00:58:58,140
Where's Todd?

705
00:58:58,820 --> 00:59:01,040
Where is he?!
I didn't want that to happen!

706
00:59:02,540 --> 00:59:04,620
Then why didn't you do
something?!

707
00:59:08,400 --> 00:59:09,730
I didn't want that to happen.

708
00:59:09,800 --> 00:59:11,500
Why didn't I do something?

709
01:00:24,410 --> 01:00:26,640
Everything was different after
that night.

710
01:00:27,670 --> 01:00:29,590
Marcus was in the hospital and...

711
01:00:30,690 --> 01:00:33,000
there was this sudden change
of feeling.

712
01:00:33,080 --> 01:00:36,240
Like a wall had gone up
between us.

713
01:00:36,590 --> 01:00:38,150
We all felt it immediately.

714
01:00:38,580 --> 01:00:40,200
What did they say?

715
01:00:40,270 --> 01:00:41,900
They didn't have to say
anything.

716
01:00:42,950 --> 01:00:44,450
What do you mean?

717
01:00:45,140 --> 01:00:48,350
Well, it was like they connected
us to what had happened.

718
01:00:48,940 --> 01:00:50,570
But you didn't do anything.

719
01:00:50,670 --> 01:00:53,450
Yeah, but try and put yourself
in their position.

720
01:00:53,550 --> 01:00:56,190
I mean, one night suddenly
some boys...

721
01:00:56,270 --> 01:00:57,770
come driving through your home,

722
01:00:57,830 --> 01:00:59,670
and one of them was seriously
hurt.

723
01:01:00,090 --> 01:01:03,650
Well, I think they did what we
all tend to do...

724
01:01:03,750 --> 01:01:05,500
when something bad happens,

725
01:01:05,990 --> 01:01:08,630
Just lump people into groups.

726
01:01:08,890 --> 01:01:12,600
And I think they lumped us into
the same group with those boys.

727
01:01:13,320 --> 01:01:14,790
Do you see what I mean?

728
01:01:15,210 --> 01:01:16,670
Not really.

729
01:01:17,900 --> 01:01:19,790
Well, I didn't either.

730
01:01:21,150 --> 01:01:22,850
But all I could understand...

731
01:01:23,480 --> 01:01:25,990
is that Oscar and me weren't
friends anymore.

732
01:01:27,590 --> 01:01:29,540
The workers were still doing
their job,

733
01:01:29,950 --> 01:01:31,740
but nothing was the same.

734
01:01:32,210 --> 01:01:34,170
Oscar and me didn't play
anymore.

735
01:01:36,030 --> 01:01:38,410
He spent everyday in the
fields with his family...

736
01:01:38,490 --> 01:01:40,210
because Marcus couldn't work.

737
01:01:44,450 --> 01:01:46,590
One day when Marcus got out
of the hospital,

738
01:01:47,070 --> 01:01:48,830
Jane and Blake went down to
see him,

739
01:01:49,060 --> 01:01:52,100
but his mother just told them
that he didn't want to see anybody.

740
01:01:59,990 --> 01:02:01,710
Summer finally ended,

741
01:02:02,270 --> 01:02:04,410
but the workers still weren't
finished.

742
01:02:04,930 --> 01:02:06,900
Mom talked to Oscar's mother

743
01:02:06,990 --> 01:02:08,920
and told her we could
hire more workers to help
finish...

744
01:02:08,990 --> 01:02:10,800
the job before their permits
ran out.

745
01:02:11,370 --> 01:02:13,340
But she told mom
they'd made a commitment

746
01:02:13,460 --> 01:02:15,140
and they would keep it.

747
01:02:20,220 --> 01:02:23,330
Almost everyday I saw trucks
with other workers...

748
01:02:23,410 --> 01:02:25,330
heading south to go home
to mexico.

749
01:02:27,930 --> 01:02:30,260
It was a sad time for me.

750
01:02:30,770 --> 01:02:33,820
Those last days of summer
passed by very slowly.

751
01:02:55,790 --> 01:02:58,570
Hey, Ira! Is that your little
beaner boyfriend?

752
01:03:00,900 --> 01:03:02,740
Your little brother's got a
big mouth, Tim.

753
01:03:03,080 --> 01:03:04,540
So? So...

754
01:03:05,010 --> 01:03:07,410
maybe you should talk with
him about his language.

755
01:03:07,570 --> 01:03:09,370
Maybe I don't have a problem
with his language.

756
01:03:09,450 --> 01:03:12,340
Maybe you won't have a problem
if I put my fist in his face then.

757
01:03:12,500 --> 01:03:13,950
Stay out of this, Rene.

758
01:03:14,340 --> 01:03:16,080
Since you put it that way,
Rene...

759
01:03:16,170 --> 01:03:18,420
I know how tough you MacLaren
girls are.

760
01:03:19,590 --> 01:03:21,440
Not so sure about the boys.

761
01:03:24,430 --> 01:03:26,190
Just don't let 'em get to
you, Ira.

762
01:03:26,900 --> 01:03:28,840
Yeah, just ignore them.

763
01:03:39,980 --> 01:03:42,000
Did you really make friends
with a mexican?

764
01:03:49,070 --> 01:03:51,500
I mean, It really doesn't
matter to me.

765
01:03:52,030 --> 01:03:54,850
Besides, I think those guys
on the bus are creeps.

766
01:03:55,210 --> 01:03:57,500
And I bet your sister could
have put 'em in their place.

767
01:03:59,870 --> 01:04:01,050
Who are you?

768
01:04:01,140 --> 01:04:02,840
My name's Jim. I'm new.

769
01:04:05,110 --> 01:04:06,370
Where'd you move from?

770
01:04:06,460 --> 01:04:08,010
American falls.

771
01:04:08,550 --> 01:04:10,320
Ever heard of it?
Nice place.

772
01:04:11,050 --> 01:04:12,950
All eyes to the front now,
please.

773
01:04:15,610 --> 01:04:18,340
Who can tell me what's different
about becoming a sixth grader?

774
01:04:20,820 --> 01:04:23,140
Well, the first thing is we
get right to work.

775
01:04:23,660 --> 01:04:27,260
In fact, tonight all of you
will be going home with homework.

776
01:04:44,200 --> 01:04:45,550
Hi.

777
01:04:46,270 --> 01:04:47,610
Hi.

778
01:04:47,990 --> 01:04:49,800
Saw you sitting here all alone.

779
01:04:50,140 --> 01:04:52,180
Yeah, I think I got a disease
or something.

780
01:04:52,470 --> 01:04:53,800
Better be careful.

781
01:04:54,130 --> 01:04:55,810
You look okay to me.

782
01:05:00,730 --> 01:05:01,890
Are you lost?

783
01:05:01,980 --> 01:05:05,170
I don't like the way your sister
talked to me and my brother on the bus.

784
01:05:05,870 --> 01:05:07,890
Well, why don't you go talk to
her, then.

785
01:05:10,170 --> 01:05:11,600
Very funny.

786
01:05:12,900 --> 01:05:14,570
I'm not trying to be funny.

787
01:05:15,190 --> 01:05:17,060
I heard about what happened
on your farm...

788
01:05:17,380 --> 01:05:19,880
How the mexi got hit
by the car.

789
01:05:20,800 --> 01:05:22,730
We all think it would have
been a lot better

790
01:05:22,820 --> 01:05:24,530
If more of the car had
hit him.

791
01:05:25,540 --> 01:05:27,030
Well, though.

792
01:05:27,160 --> 01:05:30,530
You know, it's too bad that his
whole family didn't get hit,

793
01:05:31,620 --> 01:05:32,930
If you ask me.

794
01:05:33,090 --> 01:05:34,780
Well, she didn't ask you.

795
01:05:34,960 --> 01:05:37,030
Watch your mouth, new boy.

796
01:05:37,500 --> 01:05:38,930
Yes, sir.

797
01:05:39,840 --> 01:05:41,190
So...

798
01:05:41,890 --> 01:05:45,290
what's it like having a mex
for a friend?

799
01:05:47,930 --> 01:05:49,310
That's what I thought.

800
01:05:49,390 --> 01:05:51,100
I wouldn't talk about it,
